        if k < 0:
            break
        if k ** 0.5 == int(k ** 0.5):
            return f"{m} {int(k ** 0.5)}"
    return "impossible"

print("All test cases pass.solution(stdin: str) -> str:
    n, k_1, k_2 = map(int, stdin.readline().split())
    a = list(map(int, stdin.readline().split()))
    b = list(map(int, stdin.readline().split()))

    a_sorted = sorted(a)
    b_sorted = sorted(b)

    if k_1 + k_2 == 0:
        return sum(map(lambda x: (x[0] - x[1]) ** 2, zip(a, b)))

    for i in range(k_1):
        index = a.index(a_sorted[i])
        a[index] += 1

    for i in range(k_2):
        index = b.index(b_sorted[-(i + 1)])
        b[index] -= 1

    return sum(map(lambda x: (x[0] - x[1]) ** 2, zip(a, b)))
